The paper discusses a forecasting method for time series groups using algorithms for cluster analysis, specifically the K-means algorithm. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of forecasting models based on binary trees and a modified clonal selection algorithm, which could fall under the sub-category of data mining (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the implementation of analytic dependences, which could be related to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with time series data, which could be related to the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT).
